pageContext.claim: “And if you took New York -- because New York was just -- really, they made a lot of mistakes in New York. But if you took that out -- you know, a tremendous number of deaths in New York -- if you took that out, our numbers are just about as good as anybody in the world.”
pageContext.analysis: This is false. Even removing the roughly 50,000 people who died of covid-19 in New York and New Jersey, the U.S. has still seen more people die of the disease than any other country around the world.
